## Steps to reproduce the issue

```systemverilog
// top.sv

package pkg;
    typedef enum bit [1:0] {
        CODE_NOOP = 2'd0,
        CODE_PASS = 2'd1,
        CODE_FAIL = 2'd2,
        CODE_DONE = 2'd3
    } status_code;
endpackage

module top(
    input [1:0] sin,
    output [1:0] sout,
);
    my_if u_my_if();
    a u_a(.sin, .my_if(u_my_if));
    b u_b(.sout, .my_if(u_my_if));
endmodule

interface my_if();
    pkg::status_code status;
    modport in  (input  status);
    modport out (output status);
endinterface

module a(
    input [1:0] sin,
    my_if.out my_if
);
    assign my_if.status = sin;
endmodule

module b(
    output [1:0] sout,
    my_if.in my_if
);
    assign sout = my_if.status;
endmodule
```

## Expected behavior

If `pkg::status_code status;` is changed to `bit [1:0] status;` verilog frontend is working fine
```
 Yosys 0.9+2406 (git sha1 bd2ecc2d, gcc 7.5.0-3ubuntu1~18.04 -fPIC -Os)


yosys> read_verilog -sv top.sv
1. Executing Verilog-2005 frontend: top.sv
Parsing SystemVerilog input from `top.sv' to AST representation.
Generating RTLIL representation for module `\top'.
Generating RTLIL representation for module `\my_if'.
Generating RTLIL representation for module `\a'.
top.sv:30: Warning: Identifier `\my_if.status' is implicitly declared.
Generating RTLIL representation for module `\b'.
top.sv:37: Warning: Identifier `\my_if.status' is implicitly declared.
Successfully finished Verilog frontend.
```

## Actual behavior

From yosys master
```
 Yosys 0.9+2406 (git sha1 bd2ecc2d, gcc 7.5.0-3ubuntu1~18.04 -fPIC -Os)


yosys> read_verilog -sv top.sv
1. Executing Verilog-2005 frontend: top.sv
Parsing SystemVerilog input from `top.sv' to AST representation.
Generating RTLIL representation for module `\top'.
Generating RTLIL representation for module `\my_if'.
top.sv:22: ERROR: Unknown identifier `\pkg::status_code' used as type name
```

